cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a method for generating video sequences based on generative adversarial learning, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves transferring dynamics from a source video to a target image, which could also fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of discriminator networks to validate the generated video's spatial and temporal consistency, which could also relate to graphics (cs.GR).
